4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING STATE POLICY LAWS; ALLOWING
5 FOOD SERVICE ESTABLISHMENTS TO SERVE FRESH KRATOM PRODUCTS; PROHIBITING
6 EXPIRATION DATES ON AIRLINE TRAVEL CREDITS; ASSOCIATING OWNERSHIP WITH THE
7 POSSESSOR OF THE TRAVEL CREDIT; LIMITING FEES; ALLOWING CASH REDEMPTION;
8 ESTABLISHING A FEE FOR AIRLINE TRAVEL TO AND FROM MONTANA; ESTABLISHING REPORTING
9 REQUIREMENTS; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; AMENDING SECTION 30-14-102, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN
10 IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE AND A RETROACTIVE APPLICABILITY DATE.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Kratom tea houses. A food service establishment under Title 50,
15 chapter 31, including but not limited to kratom tea houses, may prepare and serve fresh kratom products,
16 including tea, for consumption on premise.
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Termination of travel credit prohibited -- fee limitation -- redemption
19 -- airline fee -- reporting requirement. (1) A travel credit is valid until redemption and does not terminate. A
20 travel credit is considered trust property of the possessor if the issuer or seller of the travel credit declares
21 bankruptcy after issuing or selling the travel credit.
22 (2) The value represented by the travel credit belongs to the possessor and not to the issuer or
23 seller. An issuer or seller may redeem a travel credit presented by an individual whose name does not match
24 the name on the travel credit.
25 (3) A travel credit may not be reduced in value by any fee, including a dormancy fee applied if a
26 travel credit is not used.
27 (4) If the original value of the travel credit was more than $5 and the remaining value is less than
28 $5 and the possessor requests cash for the remainder, the issuer or seller shall redeem the travel credit for
